article.description: Kelsey Mitchell scored 29 points for the second night in a row, Alexa Hart added 24 and Ohio State topped No. 14 Iowa 91-85 in overtime to advance to the Big 10 Conference tournament final Sunday.
article.shortLinkText: Ohio State ousts No. 14 Iowa in Big 10 semis
article.headline: Ohio State ousts No. 14 Iowa in OT in Big 10 semifinals
article.linkText: Ohio State ousts No. 14 Iowa in Big 10 semis
article.story:
HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. -- Kelsey Mitchell scored 29 points for the second night in a row, Alexa Hart added 24 and Ohio State topped No. 14 Iowa 91-85 in overtime to advance to the Big Ten Conference tournament final Sunday.

Ohio State (23-9) will face No. 4 Maryland (29-2), winner over No. 24 Northwestern in the other semifinal Saturday.

In overtime, Whitney Jennings made a pair of free throws with 42 seconds left to draw Iowa to within one point. But on the next possession, Mitchell nailed a 3-pointer with 14 seconds left to make it a four-point game.

Jennings missed from the inside on the next trip down, and Mitchell made two free throws to seal it.

After a tightly contested second half, Hart hit one of two free throws to put Ohio State up by two with 17 seconds to go, but Bethany Doolittle's layup with three seconds left forced overtime.

The teams were tied at the half at 37.

Melissa Dixon had 22 points and Doolittle finished with 21 for Iowa (24-7).
